---
By: Heraclitus
Source:
  ID: 996c9a12-d13d-4597-a783-506d70cd1736
  Locus:
    Verse: 114
---
Those who speak with understanding must hold fast to what is common to
all as a city holds fast to its law, and even more strongly. For all
human laws are fed by the divine one. It prevails as much as it will,
and suffices for all things with something to spare.
